 anticipation, what appears in front of the investigator's eyes is not the past as it was, but the past as it will have been in relation to the time of his or her search.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDetective and mystery filmsxHistory and criticismxItaly. 0aDetective and mystery filmszItalyxHistory and criticism. 0aTime in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804786775zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804786775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804786775.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles